<BaseLayout title="Animals of Vaelinya" description="Meet the first public animals of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">World · Animals</p>
    <h1>Animals of Vaelinya</h1>
    <p class="lede">Vaelinya’s animals are living parts of place, weather, route, memory, sound, shelter, food, work, care, and ecological return.</p>
    <p>Some hum near warmth. Some rise before they fly along. Some come from the sea both ways. Some walk backwards to keep wind from their faces. Some appear only when memory, grief, route, weather, or return has reached a certain state.</p>
    <p>Each animal belongs to a place and a purpose.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">First animals</p>
      <h2>Start with five public creatures</h2>
      <p>These five give the animal section a first clear shape: small wonder, Great River water logic, elder fauna, insect symbiosis, and mythic memory.</p>
      <div class="link-list" aria-label="First public animal pages">
        <a href="/world/animals/mosskeep-frog/">Mosskeep Frog</a>
        <a href="/world/animals/rimmer-fish/">Rimmer Fish</a>
        <a href="/world/animals/hearthcrest-caller/">Hearthcrest Caller</a>
        <a href="/world/animals/amethyst-orblight/">Amethyst Orblight</a>
        <a href="/world/animals/navan-hart/">Navan Hart</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>🐾</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">How to read them</p>
        <h2>Colour, sound, movement, and place all matter</h2>
        <p>Vaelinya animals are not decorations. Their colour, sound, movement, and behaviour show how they belong to water, moss, river, weather, memory, or care.</p>
        <p>Public pages always explain that meaning in text, so readers do not need sight or hearing to understand the animal.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Animal groups</p>
      <h2>Wider animal system</h2>
      <p>The full public animal system will later include insects, birds, elder fauna, wetland creatures, fish and sea creatures, domestic animals, small mammals, reptiles, shell creatures, predators, and mythic or rare animals.</p>
      <p>These category pages should come later. The first step is to make the five strongest animals clear and readable.</p>
    </article>

